The National Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has announced that there are two new cases of coronavirus (covid-19) in Ogun and Lagos States respectively. According to the NCDC website, the new cases were confirmed in the mid hour of Tuesday. NCDC twitted: 2 new cases of #COVID19 have been confirmed in Nigeria. 1 is in Lagos State & 1 in Ogun One case is a returning traveler. The second case is contact of a previously confirmed case As at 1 pm on March 24, there are 42 confirmed cases of #COVID19 in Nigeria-2 discharged, 1 death. ALSO READ: Coronavirus: Kaduna correctional service suspends visits to centres SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!!